One aspect of accessibility is to add alt to the pictures provided, which allow the extension to read the content.
<img src="profile.jpg" alt="Tong Ning profile photo" />

Ensured sufficient color contrast between text and background. For most of the time, I use black words on the white background. I also provide dark mode, which allows white words on the black background.
// in .jsx
function toggleDarkMode() {
  document.documentElement.classList.toggle('dark');
}
// in .html
<button onClick={toggleDarkMode}>Toggle Dark Mode</button>
